The paper focuses on AutoProof, an auto-active verifier for object-oriented sequential programs with complex functional specifications. Additionally, the paper mentions AutoProof's support for advanced object-oriented features, which suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. The paper also discusses AutoProof's methodology for framing and class invariants, which suggests that it may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. Furthermore, the paper deals with functional verification, which suggests that it may belong to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) category. Finally, the paper discusses AutoProof's performance on benchmark problems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) category.
